pullRequest.body:
This provides the fact that the norm of scaling a matrix of quaternions by a quaternion is bounded by the product of the norms.

Can you add this for the operator norm (from `EuclideanSpace`) too? It's in `Analysis.NormedSpace.Star.Matrix`

> Can you add this for the operator norm (from `EuclideanSpace`) too? It's in `Analysis.NormedSpace.Star.Matrix`

There's not really any point, because that uses `[IsROrC ùïú]` and so there is no case where `BoundedSMul` is true and `NormedSpace` isn't.

Ok, I guess it would be statable, but we're missing the corresponding instances on the operator norm on continuous linear maps:
```lean
theorem instL2OpNBoundedSmul [SeminormedRing R] [Module R ùïú] [SMulCommClass ùïú R ùïú]
    [BoundedSMul R ùïú] : BoundedSMul R (Matrix m n ùïú) :=
  .of_norm_smul_le fun r x => by
    rw [l2_op_norm_def]
    -- fails, no `BoundedSMul` instance
    have := norm_smul_le r ((toEuclideanLin (ùïú := ùïú) (m := m) (n := n)).trans toContinuousLinearMap x)
    -- need a `map_smul_of_tower` lemma that is missing
    sorry
```
In the end this would only give us the actions by `Rat` and `Int` anyway, I would guess.

Thanks. I'll add the bounded smul myself for continuous linear maps if I remember.
